The paper discusses the problem of bias in datasets used in the analytics industry and proposes a method for removing bias from data. This is a topic that is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), cryptography and security (cs.CR), cybernetics (cs.CY), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, given that the proposed method involves the use of adversarial networks, which are commonly used in machine learning, it is most likely to belong to the cs.LG sub-category.
